//www.vancouver.com/movies/hollywood_north/vancouver_film_industry_overview/index.htm|archive-date=2008-05-17|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n[[CHAN-DT|Global BC]] is the most popular evening newscast in the city, though [[CIVT-DT|CTV Vancouver]], currently second in the ratings, has aggressively been trying to increase its market share \u2014 including the purchasing of a news helicopter known as 'Chopper 9'. In 2006, Global BC launched the Global One traffic helicopter for live traffic updates and breaking news. [[CBUT-DT|CBC]] also has local newscasts though they are far back in the ratings.{{Citation needed|date=December 2007}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=\"100%\"\n!{{nowrap|OTA [[virtual channel]]}}<br>([[Program and System Information Protocol|PSIP]])\n!OTA channel\n![[Shaw Communications|Shaw Cable]]\n!{{nowrap|[[EastLink (company)|Delta Cable]]}}\n!scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 90px;\"|Call Sign\n!Network\n!Notes\n|-\n|2.1\n|43 ([[ultra high frequency|UHF]])\n|3\n|3\n|[[CBUT-DT]]\n|[[CBC Television]]\n|\n|-\n|6.1\n|49 ([[ultra high frequency|UHF]])\n|6\n|6\n|[[CHEK-DT]]\n|[[Independent station (North America)|Independent]]/[[Yes TV]]\n|Transmitted from [[Victoria, British Columbia|Victoria]]\n|-\n|8.1\n|22 ([[ultra high frequency|UHF]])\n|11\n|11\n|[[CHAN-DT]]\n|[[Global Television Network|Global]]\n|\n|-\n|10.1\n|33 ([[ultra high frequency|UHF]])\n|13\n|13\n|[[CKVU-DT]]\n|[[Citytv]]\n|\n|-\n|12.1\n|rowspan=4|35 ([[ultra high frequency|UHF]])\n|&ndash;\n|&ndash;\n|rowspan=4|[[KVOS-TV]]\n|[[Heroes & Icons]]\n|{{nowrap|Transmitted from [[Bellingham, Washington]]; targeted at Canadian audiences and maintains sales office in Vancouver}}\n|-\n|12.2\n|&ndash;\n|&ndash;\n|[[Movies!]]\n|Transmitted from Bellingham, Washington; [[Digital subchannel|subchannel]] of KVOS-TV\n|-\n|12.3\n|30\n|52\n|[[Me-TV]]\n|Transmitted from Bellingham, Washington; subchannel of KVOS-TV\n|-\n|12.4\n|&ndash;\n|&ndash;\n|[[Decades (TV network)|Decades]]\n|Transmitted from Bellingha